

Prerequisites
Docker Desktop must be installed and running (you should see the whale icon in your taskbar).
PowerShell must be run as Administrator.


// step 1. install choco package manager in widows using PowerShell as an Administrator

1. Copy and paste below command in powershell

Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force; [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072; iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://community.chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))

2. check choco version so that we can verify it is installed or not 

PS C:\Users\piyush_kumar> choco -v
2.3.0


Once choco is install now we will install kubectl for windows using chocolatey

// step 2. install kubectl  using choco

1. choco install kubernetes-cli

verify it is installed or not 

2. PS C:\Users\piyush_kumar> kubectl version --client
Client Version: v1.32.2
Kustomize Version: v5.5.0


Once Kubectl is installed now we are installing minikube on windows using chocolatey

// step 3.  install chocolatey using choco

1. choco install minikube

now check minikube is installed or not using 

2. check minikube version  

you should see like PS C:\Users\piyush_kumar> minikube version
minikube version: v1.33.0
commit: 86fc9d54fca63f295d8737c8eacdbb7987e89c67

if you are not seeing this it means you are getting error 

so for fixing do one thing follow below steps carefully 

Press Windows Key and search for "env".
Select Edit the system environment variables.
Click the Environment Variables button.
In the top section (User variables), double-click Path.
Click New and paste:
C:\Users\piyush_kumar\AppData\Roaming\npm\lib\Minikube\tools
Click OK on all windows.

after this once you  do 

PS C:\Users\piyush_kumar> minikube version
minikube version: v1.33.0
commit: 86fc9d54fca63f295d8737c8eacdbb7987e89c67

you will see this thing above on your powershell 


Step 3: Start the Cluster
Now that the software is installed, you need to turn the "virtual computer" on.
code
Powershell
minikube start --driver=docker


Step 4: Verify Everything is Working
Check if your node is running:
kubectl get nodes

and now you are ready 

PS C:\Users\piyush_kumar> kubectl get nodes
NAME       STATUS   ROLES           AGE   VERSION
minikube   Ready    control-plane   17s   v1.30.0


==> start your work 


